The paper deals with approximation algorithms for graph problems, which is a topic that falls under several CS sub-categories. The use of structural graph algorithms and the focus on graph classes that are algorithmically tractable suggest that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely sub-category. The development of new editing algorithms for graphs also suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible sub-category. The paper also deals with optimization problems and approximation ratios, which are topics that fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper's focus on graph problems and approximation algorithms suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category.
